Package soot.dotnet.members

Class ByReferenceWrapperGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • soot.dotnet.members.ByReferenceWrapperGenerator
  • public class ByReferenceWrapperGenerator
extends Object
    Parameters in .NET can be passed by reference. Since Jimple does not support this semantic, we generate Wrapper classes to pass instead. Note that .NET (as of right now, mid 2024) does not support co- or contravariants in parameters and return types. As such, overriding virtual methods does not pose a problem when we substitute parameters with reference wrappers.
    Author:
    Marc Miltenberger
